        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 25 at 2:40PM EDT until July 25 at 3:45PM EDT by NWS Pittsburgh PA</headline>
        <description>At 240 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 10 miles northeast
of Hundred, or 11 miles southwest of Waynesburg, moving east at 25
mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Department of Highways reported numerous trees down
across Marshall County.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Star City, Granville, Hundred, Cassville, Rogersville, Bobtown,
Nemacolin, Aleppo, Blacksville, Spraggs, Mount Morris, New
Freeport, Pentress, Brave, Daybrook, Wana, Core, Wadestown and
Osage.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm has produced damaging winds and is capable of
producing large hail.

Continuous cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning is one of nature's leading killers. Remember, if you can
hear thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead
to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
